[[Möbius space|Projective model of Möbius geometry]] $$Q\setminus\{[p]\}$$ with the metric given by

$$
d_\mathrm{eucl}([x],[y])^2=
-2 \frac
{\langle x,y\rangle_{n+1,1}}
{\langle x,p\rangle_{n+1,1} \langle y,p\rangle_{n+1,1}}
$$

is isometric to $$\R^n$$ with the euclidean metric.